				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Please give your view :)<a name="70505"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 1 04 12:03 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, Daniel, I applaud your efforts to defend everyones &quot;geek-hood&quot; that plays EQ.  However, I have to somewhat agree with the &quot;quitees.&quot;  Everquest, from what I have learned from personal experience, is more of a way of life than a game.  I have been playing on and off for Four years, after one of my close friends MADE me start it up(he beat me in SC, which was a first).  Anyway, after these four years I don't really enjoy everquest, I NEED everquest.  When I think if things I wanna do on everquest I dont say &quot;I wanna get 63!! That would be great!&quot; I say, &quot;I need to get 64&quot;.  The keyword being NEED.  It 's more like a chore than anything else.  
<br />

<br />
When I start playing everquest again after a long break I start to become enthralled with it again.  I usually start off saying &quot;Okay I'll only play an hour a night.&quot; Within a week or two its up to two and three hours a night, eventually even 4 and 5.  This is unacceptable for me, I have 1.) A Part time job 2.) 18 Credit Hours of School 3.) A Girlfriend who lives with me(which is the most extruciating, humilating, degrating, and all other negative descriptive words, job that anyone could ever have)  4.) And a dog. The dog is not like a normal dog, he's like a CHILD, thanks to my GF.  Anyway, when I am playing I stop wanting to go out to parties and what not with my friends and of course that causes my GF to suffer because she generally does not go anywhere without me.  
<br />

<br />
When I quit, however, my life is full of good times, in a strictly Non-pixelated way.  I hooked up with my gf when I wasn't playing (blind date at a party, later she asked me to her prom and well, everyone knows about prom nite parties.)  Yes, Daniel, I generally do things like Drink(as in alcohol) and RARELY some non-legal drug.  However, I was a full blown POT head my senior year of high school while I was playing EQ.  EQ has no bearings on drug use, this is from personal experience, I used to watch my friend snort an OC(oxy cotton) and then go play his SK on EQ.  EQ also interferes with my personal health.  During my junior years of high school I was a very talented soccer player, until i sustained a nasty knee injury.  However, I soon recovered and was on the way to being a good player again until I got into EQ.  I became out of shape, out of touch with my skills, and I have asthma which worsens when I am not physically up to par(not weight wise, stamina wise).  
<br />

<br />
So let me put it you frankly:
<br />

<br />
Eq is a great game to play, but everyone needs to have an outlet, some sort of hobby, and a limit.  YOU NEED TO TAKE BREAKS.  I cannot stress that enough.  The h*ll with flagging your character for planar access, I guarantee you when you come back the planes will still be there and if your guild surpassed you, find a new one.  Don't let EQ overrun your entire life, especially if you're still a teenager(which, by reading your first post, I am guessing you are).  If your under 18, go have fun for god sakes.  Save EQ for the late night after a party.  Play it half drunk.  But these are the best years, you need to go out and meet some girls(and guys for you girls), have fun <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />, and beat some people up =).
<br />

<br />
Resil Darksong
<br />
63 Bard Of Tunare 
<br />

<br />
EDIT: Age 20  </span></td>
