				<td colspan="2"><span>Simply put,
<br />

<br />
RL &gt; EQ.
<br />

<br />
EQ = ANY other hobby (&lt;insert your hobby name here&gt;), no more, no less (with the exception of having good sex  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" /> )
<br />

<br />
The problem with EQ (or any other hobby) is that when people&#180;s lifes get fooked up, some of them resort to EQ as a way to forget their screwed up life. In that respect, drinking, doing drugs, or even playing soccer is just as bad. Again, no more, no less. Once you are done with EQ, drinking, drug haze offes, or soccer game gets over with, you are back to your screwed up life you didn&#180;t take care of, which continues to be fooked up cause you chose to hide your head under the sand instead of facing your problems and fixing your life, either by palying EQ, drinking, or any of the before mentioned hobbies.
<br />

<br />
Eventually, those who finally get around to fix their lifes, either by choice or by chance, computer breaking up, they tend to regard the hobby they chose to hide upon as the worst thing ever in their lifes, instead of blaming themselves for not getting out of the self-destructive loop sooner, by themselves or by seeking the help of others.
<br />

<br />
If EQ, or any other hobby is not used as a &quot;hiding&quot; from RL tool, then as far as you enjoy it, go for it. The only but I would add is that, if you are a teenager, and still developping your social skills, EQ or any &quot;solo&quot; hobby, could hinder further developping of social interaction, which can affect you later on in life. Why I said sex is prolly the exception to the rule, not cause I am a pervert, but cause it not only allows for social interaction, but you feel da*n good about yourself, as well as boosting your self-steem.
<br />

<br />
If you have to chose between EQ &lt;insert hobby here&gt;  or RL, because of lack of self control, then RL &gt; all. Work &gt; No money in the bank (money = freedom of choice). Friends &gt; Hobbies.
<br />

<br />
But there is really no reason while you can&#180;t combine the 2 of them. If your social and working-study life is pretty time intensive, then you will have very little time left for EQ play. As long as you keep your priorities straight, everyone should be allowed to have at least 2 hours a week of own-personal time, even if kids, wife, work and all. 
<br />

<br />
My 2 cp.
<br />

<br />
EDIT: 34 years old.</span></td>
