				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Please give your view :)<a name="70541"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Dec 2 04 12:07 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>This has turned into an interesting thread.  I'll have to agree that EQ can do a lot to ruin life balance if you let it, but you can also enjoy EQ as part of a fun life.
<br />

<br />
I was fortunate because I'd never been a gamer when I started playing.  I started because everyone at my karate school played and my husband had gotten sick and needed a diversion.  While he was battling to get his Graves Disease under control and couldn't windsurf, go out on the Hobie, or run, he played EQ all the time.  It was better than staring out the window at the ocean and knowing his heart would beat out of his chest if he tried to do the things he truly loved.  I played simply to join him in his new-found hobby.  My karate instructor had a guild and everyone in the guild put martial arts, work, and real life above the game.  
<br />

<br />
If you play with people who share your sense of balance and even who share your RL hobby, it helps keep the game in its proper place.  I eventually joined a raiding guild and we're in the top end of the game (Txevu in GoD, one d*mn puppy from Anguish in Omens), but I chose the guild because raid times are only 3 days a week and don't conflict with my karate schedule.  The guild is filled primarily with other adults who work for a living and have families and other priorities.
<br />

<br />
Learning to moderate your life is an important skill.  Learn it as young as you can and keep practicing.
<br />

<br />
Calli
<br />

<br />
(Age 29, software design analyst, tournament kickboxer, avid hiker, former windsurfer (I moved to Boulder, CO so no more ocean<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-6.gif" border="0" alt="Sad" hspace="2" />), novice skate skier, and 3-night-a-week EQ player)
<br />

<br />
Oh yeah.  I don't own a TV either.  That helps too.</span></td>
